tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild hypoglycemia and significantly elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function. LDL cholesterol is slightly above the recommended range. Other parameters, including liver enzymes, electrolytes, and proteins, are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation for renal impairment and monitoring of glucose and lipid profile.
